articles.text:
Several reactions trail on social media as APC Leader, Asiwaju Bola Tinubu secretly returns to Nigerian from London medical trip.

Sources close to the Former Governor of Lagos state said Tinubu came in this evening, Friday, 8 October 2021 to beat his campaign group, SWAGA 2023 to the rally planned for Sunday, 10 October 2023, when they were hoping to receive him with a mother of all rallies that will shake the nation.

“Asiwaju is not disposed to the elaborate rally planned to receive him by his supporters because of the mood of the nation, that’s why he came in quietly, unannounced,” said a source who craves anonymity.

See some reactions gathered on social media after his arrival in Nigeria from UK.

@Koofhurray wrote, “What that means is that Nigeria will be moving from one London treatment seeker to another for a president. That will be doom.”

@Opalpeach wrote, “He for just Dey there for thesame reasons forever……..person wey never become president wey don Dey travel for months medical care, I hope this wouldn’t become the whole federation burden later.”

@Oyeyemiyinka wrote, “This country is messed up. To think he govern a whole lagos biggest economic zone in Africa and left with no world class hospital to take care of him. A Waste”

A popular music producer, Samklef wrote, “With free and fair election Na only lagos go give tinubu vote his apc members. Only sick people will vote for him. Sick country.“
